<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 07 at 8:01AM EST  by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...HEAVY LAKE EFFECT SNOW WILL IMPACT THE MORNING COMMUTE
ALONG SOUTH SHORE OF LAKE ONTARIO...
At 8:00 AM a west to east oriented lake effect snow band was
slowly dropping south along and toward the south shore of Lake
Ontario. This band will continue south coming onshore in Orleans,
Monroe and Wayne counties over the next hour. Periods of heavy
snow, with snowfall rates of over 1 inch per hour will be
possible. Sudden reductions in visibility to a half mile or less
will be possible at times.
If driving allow extra time to reach your destination, and be
prepare for rapidly changing conditions.</description>
